review_blob: I enjoyed this beer.  For being 7 percent alc. it went down smooth without any chemical or alcohol taste.  It actually went down like it was a lite beer, which impressed the hell out of me in that it has such a high alc content.  This would be my beer of choice if it came in 30 packs for $15.99.

I must say, for the money this is by far the best beer out there.  I can get 12 cans for under 6 bucks, and every can goes down smooth.  I like to pop open second opening with my can opener which makes the beer go down even smoother.  A true party beer.

The aroma is sweet with a hint of citrus, and is usually served with several lemon wedges. The appearance is cloudy gold unfiltered. The flavor is not bitter, real smooth, with a citrus aftertaste, and really seems to coat my tongue with a nice creamy film.  This is my favorite of the Bohemian Brewery beers and usually drink a half gallon with my pork schnitzel.
Great flavor with mild bitterness.  Goes down smooth.  Flavor similar to Coors Light except that Kona is smoother and more enjoyable to drink.
Not Henrys best beer.  I like the golden lager better.  This one is my least favorite in the Hefeweizen class.  A lemon wedge is a necessity.

I am not a big fan of the bottle.  It appears that the company has recently changed its label, which is an improvement.  The taste is excellent for a beer under a buck a bottle.  This is my favorite beer for the price.

I had to drive to 4 different locations in Utah to find this beer.  For reasons I cant explain, I wanted a good Mexican Beer.  The only complaint I have about this beer was the price.  It was $1.70/bottle.  I drink it with a lime wedge and watch the sunset.
